{"id":28819,"date":"2019-05-08T10:31:17","date_gmt":"2019-05-08T06:31:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=28819"},"modified":"2019-05-20T15:02:58","modified_gmt":"2019-05-20T11:02:58","slug":"revealed-halal-haram-food","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/08\/revealed-halal-haram-food\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Food: Allah reveals Halal and Haram food"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu al-Sha\u2019tha reported: Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThe people of the time of ignorance would eat some things and leave other things believing they were unclean. Allah sent his Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and revealed his book allowing what is lawful and forbidding what is unlawful. What is allowed in it is lawful, and what is forbidden in it is unlawful. Whatever it is silent upon is an act of clemency.\u201d Then he recited the verse, \u201c<strong>Say: I do not find in what was revealed to me anything forbidden to eat except dead animals, blood poured forth, or the flesh of swine,<\/strong>\u201d (6:145) until the end of the verse.<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 3800<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0651\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062b\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062c\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0650\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e\u0629\u0650 \u064a\u064e\u0623\u0652\u0643\u064f\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0634\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0648\u064e\u064a\u064